{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 34,
  "title": "第三十四章（成大）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "道渢呵，亓可左右也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "成功遂事，而弗名有也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "萬物歸焉，而弗為主。"
    },
    {
      "text": "則："
    },
    {
      "text": "恆无欲也，可名於小。"
    },
    {
      "text": "萬物歸焉，而弗為主，可名於大。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人之能成大也，"
    },
    {
      "text": "以亓不為大也，故能成大。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言道氾氾，若浮若沉，若有若無，視之不見，說之難殊。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 4,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道可左可右，無所不宜。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "恃，待也。萬物皆待道而生。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道不辭謝而逆止也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "有道不名其有功也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道雖愛養萬物，不如人主有所收取。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 1,
          "end": 2
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道匿德藏名，怕然無為，似若微小也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物皆歸道受氣，道非如人主有所禁止也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物橫來橫去，使名自在，故可名於大也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 12,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人法道匿德藏名，不為滿大。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 12,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人以身師導，不言而化，萬事修治，故能成其大。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言道氾濫，無所不適，可左右上下周旋而用，則無所不至也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物皆由道而生，既生而不知所由，故天下常無欲之時，萬物各得其所，若道無施於物，故名於小矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物皆歸之以生，而力使不知其所由，此不為小，故復可名於大矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 12,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "為大於其細，圖難於其易。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
